20:23.600 --> 20:26.194
Are there any relatives
by that name?

20:27.240 --> 20:31.074
She's a teenager. Okay, thank you.
I'm sorry to bother you.

20:32.000 --> 20:33.991
Hello, is Lisa there?

20:34.080 --> 20:36.753
Who is this?
-This is Toby Logan.

20:36.840 --> 20:38.717
I'm a paramedic in Toronto.

20:40.880 --> 20:43.952
Is Lisa all right?
Did something happen to her?

20:45.360 --> 20:46.634
No.

20:46.720 --> 20:49.553
Are you Lisa Greyson's mother?
-Yes.

20:52.280 --> 20:57.195
Margaret Greyson. Please, I'm her mother.
Tell me if something's happened to her.

20:58.080 --> 21:01.789
No, no. I mean, I don't know.

21:06.240 --> 21:10.392
I don't understand.
Why are you calling here?

21:12.080 --> 21:15.675
Do you know my daughter?
-No. No.

21:16.560 --> 21:19.597
I just wanted to call to...

21:21.200 --> 21:24.317
This conversation is over. Goodbye.

21:36.080 --> 21:37.877
Who's Lisa Greyson?

21:41.680 --> 21:43.910
Your name is Toby. Say it.
-Toby.

21:44.000 --> 21:46.673
Toby Logan. Say it again.
-Toby Logan.

21:47.320 --> 21:50.278
That's the only name
you've ever had, okay?

22:02.360 --> 22:06.035
Is that tight? It's tight,
right?

22:07.400 --> 22:09.391
What?
-Mr Bey!

22:10.400 --> 22:12.994
Mr Bey, you got
yourself a package here.

22:13.080 --> 22:14.354
My demos.

22:18.640 --> 22:20.551
It's my demos. Thank you.

22:20.640 --> 22:22.312
Would you please?

22:24.120 --> 22:27.749
Oh, baby! There you go. Oh, man.

22:27.840 --> 22:30.035
Hey, Les, this could be worth
something one day. Enjoy.

22:30.120 --> 22:31.473
"I'm Gonna Thrill Again. "

22:31.560 --> 22:33.949
Yeah. You know, "Thrill again."
It's like, "Kill again."

22:34.040 --> 22:36.508
It's a play on words.
Hey, sir, you want one of my demos?

22:40.280 --> 22:42.840
Hello? You're mad.

22:44.560 --> 22:48.235
Right now? Okay, I'm on my way.

22:49.880 --> 22:52.713
I see your little shadow's here again.
-I invited him.

22:53.920 --> 22:54.955
What is it this time?

22:55.040 --> 22:57.600
I'm working a case, and Toby
happens to be involved in it.

22:57.680 --> 22:59.193
Happens to be involved?

22:59.280 --> 23:03.159
Or maybe it's more that he just put himself right
in the middle of it, like he always does?

23:03.240 --> 23:07.438
What difference does it make? I mean,
if he's got information, I'm gonna use it.

23:07.520 --> 23:09.636
Right.
-Anything else?

23:10.480 --> 23:11.913
No.

23:12.280 --> 23:13.429
Hey, there.

23:13.520 --> 23:16.637
I was just coming to get you.
-Good. Well, I saved you the trouble.

23:16.720 --> 23:17.789
So, I'm at the front desk

23:17.880 --> 23:20.917
and another detective is talking
about some woman from White Rock, BC,

23:21.000 --> 23:24.197
who got a prank call from
some clown named Toby Logan.

23:24.280 --> 23:27.272
Okay, it wasn't a prank call.
-Thank you.

23:27.360 --> 23:28.793
She's here?
-Yeah.

23:28.880 --> 23:30.871
In the conference room.

23:36.120 --> 23:38.236
Tell me about her daughter.

23:38.320 --> 23:40.959
Okay, I think that Daniel might
have killed her daughter.

23:41.040 --> 23:42.314
Do you have any solid evidence

23:42.400 --> 23:43.549
or proof of this?
-No.

23:43.640 --> 23:45.119
Well, you can't go in
there and tell her that.

23:45.200 --> 23:48.954
What am I supposed to say?
-Margaret, this is Toby Logan.

23:49.840 --> 23:50.989
Toby.

23:52.960 --> 23:54.518
I'm sorry.

23:54.600 --> 23:58.195
PIease, just tell me what you know
about my daughter's whereabouts.

23:58.280 --> 23:59.872
I don't know where she is.

23:59.960 --> 24:01.473
Careful, Toby.

24:02.600 --> 24:05.398
I don't.
-Then tell us what you do know.

24:08.280 --> 24:10.953
Someone bought Lisa
a bus ticket home.

24:13.360 --> 24:15.351
But she didn't get there.

24:17.520 --> 24:19.590
I think it's a possibility...

24:20.800 --> 24:24.110
This is just what I think here.
-Go on.

24:26.040 --> 24:31.717
Please.
-Well, I think that she could be...

24:31.800 --> 24:34.473
She might be in some
kind of trouble.

24:40.480 --> 24:43.916
Mrs Greyson, did Lisa ever
mention a kid named Daniel?

24:46.720 --> 24:48.358
I don't think so.

24:50.120 --> 24:53.908
Will this Daniel know where she is?
-I'm not sure.

24:55.400 --> 24:57.550
Can I talk to this Daniel?

24:58.120 --> 25:00.270
Ball's in your court, Logan.

25:04.520 --> 25:06.875
Hey. What's up?
-It's that time.

25:14.280 --> 25:15.429
Nice.

25:35.560 --> 25:38.313
Hey, Daniel. Daniel.

25:39.520 --> 25:43.877
What the hell do you want, skid mark?
-Just want you to meet someone.

25:45.080 --> 25:49.232
I'm Detective Charlie Marks.
I just want to ask you a few questions.

25:50.000 --> 25:52.116
Do you know a Lisa Greyson?

25:56.240 --> 25:57.355
Lisa!

26:03.960 --> 26:05.075
Mom.

26:05.560 --> 26:06.754
Lisa?

26:10.800 --> 26:15.954
Lisa. Thank God you're alive!
When I didn't hear from you, I thought...

26:17.360 --> 26:19.874
What have you done to yourself?

26:25.280 --> 26:31.355
Mom, I'm Daniel now.
-Sweetie, you're making a terrible mistake.

26:32.440 --> 26:33.839
You're too young to make
a decision like this.

26:33.920 --> 26:35.672
I've known since I was six.

26:35.760 --> 26:38.877
You could change your mind.
And there's therapy.

26:39.720 --> 26:44.589
They could discover a drug.
If you do this, there's no going back.

26:44.880 --> 26:46.154
You don't understand.

26:46.240 --> 26:51.314
Look, we'll go home. We'll talk.
We'll get you back on anti-depressants.

26:51.400 --> 26:55.678
I'm not depressed any more, Mom.
-My baby girl, I thought I lost you.

26:56.960 --> 26:58.552
You've lost your daughter, Mom,

26:58.640 --> 27:03.031
and unless you can accept that,
you're gonna lose me, too.

27:04.400 --> 27:08.518
Maybe if we go back to the church.
Lisa, you can't do this!

27:08.600 --> 27:11.876
You still don't understand.
You'll never understand.

27:38.360 --> 27:42.638
He's gone. I don't know where he is.
-What are you going to do?

27:43.520 --> 27:46.159
We found your missing child.
The rest is up to you.

27:46.240 --> 27:49.073
Or I can give you a ride back
to the hotel if you want.

27:49.160 --> 27:51.435
You coming?
-I'll be a minute.

28:28.240 --> 28:30.629
Man, I could not imagine
wanting to get a sex change.

28:30.720 --> 28:32.392
I'm a guy, you know? It's perfect.

28:32.480 --> 28:35.870
I don't have to smell good.
I don't have to pluck anything.

28:35.960 --> 28:39.236
It's amazing to me that you
don't have a girlfriend.

28:39.320 --> 28:40.799
Dude, shut up.

28:44.120 --> 28:45.951
I can relate to what
this kid's going through.

28:46.040 --> 28:47.837
Say what?
-Having to hide who you really are

28:47.920 --> 28:49.831
from your friends,
your family, the whole world.

28:49.920 --> 28:51.069
I completely understand that.

28:51.160 --> 28:53.230
And then I come around,
this kid's got a brand-new Iife,

28:53.320 --> 28:54.389
and I ruin it for him.

28:54.480 --> 28:56.277
Toby, don't worry about it.
We'll find him, okay?

28:56.360 --> 28:59.557
No, Oz, I gotta stop getting
into people's Iives.

28:59.880 --> 29:04.032
You know, I have said that before.
-When?

29:04.600 --> 29:06.716
Doesn't it sound like something I'd say?
-No.

29:15.360 --> 29:18.352
Find Daniel yet?
-No, no, I'm having a hard time.

29:18.440 --> 29:19.668
You think you can help me out here?

29:19.760 --> 29:22.115
It's not a police matter,
it's for social services.

29:22.200 --> 29:26.273
You know, if Ramone gets to him first,
he's going to be all over him.

29:26.360 --> 29:29.238
You're a cop. You've been to where he hangs.

29:29.680 --> 29:33.070
Okay, well, maybe you got a point.

29:33.160 --> 29:36.789
Maybe we did a good thing and maybe
Daniel stayed away from Ramone.

29:36.880 --> 29:38.552
No, he can't. He won't.

29:38.640 --> 29:43.395
He needs to get more steroids first.
You know he's not cut out for the streets.

29:45.400 --> 29:47.470
Girl-to-boy transgenders
need testosterone.

29:47.560 --> 29:50.313
Daniel's been shooting steroids
because that's all he can get.

29:50.400 --> 29:53.597
So, that's why he's hitting the drugstores,
to get what he needs.

29:53.680 --> 29:57.275
AII right, I'll write a report.
We find Daniel, we'll bring him in.

29:57.360 --> 29:59.749
So, it's not enough
to shake down Ramone,

29:59.840 --> 30:02.400
and in the process,
ask him where Daniel is?

30:02.480 --> 30:04.948
Do you think he's going to tell us?

30:07.080 --> 30:10.277
Logan, you hear me?
-Yeah.

30:11.880 --> 30:14.348
I hear you.
-Come on, Logan!

30:14.440 --> 30:16.556
You gotta let me do my job.

30:19.160 --> 30:20.275
He didn't hear me.

30:20.520 --> 30:23.956
So, this Daniel is Lisa?
-Yeah.

30:24.720 --> 30:27.553
She pretended to leave,
then came back as Daniel.

30:27.640 --> 30:33.112
And then I guess he told people that he
killed Lisa to gain some kind of respect.

30:34.120 --> 30:35.792
I wish she would have told me.

30:35.880 --> 30:38.917
Well, maybe she felt she
couldn't tell anybody.

30:39.920 --> 30:43.117
This guy, Baggy.
I think he knows where Daniel is.

30:46.160 --> 30:48.390
Sorry. I wish I could help you.

30:49.920 --> 30:51.592
All right, thanks.

30:52.240 --> 30:56.358
The ride was so scary!
Know when you get butterflies? Crazy!

30:56.440 --> 30:57.793
Hey, Cuz.

30:58.800 --> 31:03.157
I need you to help me find Daniel.
You knew all along, didn't you?

31:04.920 --> 31:06.114
You knew about Daniel and Lisa.

31:06.200 --> 31:08.475
That's why you didn't want
to talk to me about it.

31:08.560 --> 31:12.758
I need to find where Baggy is,
'cause if I don't,

31:12.840 --> 31:16.753
this time it won't just be Lisa who's dead,
it might be Daniel.

31:18.600 --> 31:19.715
Cuz.

31:20.440 --> 31:23.557
Hey, fellows.
What can I do for you?

31:24.080 --> 31:25.911
You guys want some V?

31:27.600 --> 31:29.830
I said 10 bucks a pop, right?

31:32.680 --> 31:35.069
You fellows take care, now.

31:35.160 --> 31:36.878
Where's Daniel?

31:37.600 --> 31:39.556
I know about Ramone
and the drugstores.

31:40.120 --> 31:43.556
We do it tonight.
-I'm with you.

31:45.080 --> 31:46.399
No, man, I don't really know.

31:46.480 --> 31:49.233
You don't know. You don't
really know? Where's Daniel?

31:49.920 --> 31:51.638
Daniel goes down tonight.

32:03.160 --> 32:07.551
Hey, Oz. Come meet me at my place.
They're going to kill Daniel tonight.

32:22.600 --> 32:23.874
Full yet?

32:28.520 --> 32:30.078
How do we even know
this is the place?

32:30.160 --> 32:31.559
It's Ramone's hood.

32:31.640 --> 32:34.200
I've seen the shamrock.
-Okay, you're the telepath.

32:34.280 --> 32:35.679
Well, I don't know how
else to find Daniel.

32:35.760 --> 32:39.548
Hopefully, Ramone will lead us to him and
the pharmacy they're going to break into.

32:39.640 --> 32:41.790
Okay, I get that part,
but then what do we do?

32:41.880 --> 32:45.270
Well, we're going to go in there and get
him out of there before something happens.

32:45.360 --> 32:49.114
Personally, I think we should
just call Detective Marks on this.

32:49.200 --> 32:50.838
Well, I have.
I left her a few messages.

32:50.920 --> 32:54.754
And? And that's why
we're sitting in my car

32:54.840 --> 32:57.229
in front of the place that
Ramone supposedly hangs out.

32:57.320 --> 32:59.675
You're so smart.
-Yeah.

32:59.760 --> 33:01.751
Where you going?
-I'm hungry.

33:01.840 --> 33:03.478
You just ate half a
convenience store.

33:03.560 --> 33:06.916
Well, when I'm bored I eat.
-Do you get bored a lot?

33:08.080 --> 33:10.071
Is that a fat joke?
-Bye.

33:23.040 --> 33:24.598
Hey, Ramone.

33:28.280 --> 33:32.831
Okay, so you're paying off security
guards for alarm codes. Nice, Ramone.

33:39.400 --> 33:40.719
Sorry, Oz.

33:43.720 --> 33:46.792
Yo, Baggy, is this on or what?
-Yeah, it's on.

33:46.880 --> 33:48.313
Then, what the hell?
Where is everyone?

33:48.400 --> 33:52.439
I gave them the night off.
-Ramone?

33:54.200 --> 33:57.636
The security codes. Get to work.

34:11.320 --> 34:13.675
You ready for this, Baggy?
-Yeah.

34:14.159 --> 34:15.956
Yeah? Good.

34:19.000 --> 34:20.752
Who, me?
-Yeah.

34:21.520 --> 34:25.353
I changed my mind. I think it's
time you got your hands dirty.

34:25.440 --> 34:27.431
Show me what type of nuts you got.

34:27.520 --> 34:29.192
All right?
-Yeah.

35:13.560 --> 35:14.709
Hello?

35:16.040 --> 35:17.189
When?

35:18.960 --> 35:20.518
Damn it, Logan!

35:26.600 --> 35:29.034
What took you so long?
-It was dark.

35:29.600 --> 35:32.797
What the hell, Ramone?
-"What the hell?" Watch your mouth.

35:32.880 --> 35:36.236
I'm thinking maybe you got a couple of vials
you're holding off for your best customer?

35:36.320 --> 35:37.514
You wouldn't be doing that,
would you?

35:37.600 --> 35:39.238
No, man. You know I give
you all my business.

35:41.720 --> 35:43.790
What do we have here?
Is that the deal?

35:43.880 --> 35:46.519
So, you gonna rat me out,
get yourself a free ride

35:46.600 --> 35:49.478
and then start up the deal all over again,
huh? Is that what you think?

35:49.560 --> 35:52.074
No, look, I never told the cops anything!
-You're lying.

35:52.160 --> 35:54.116
Listen, okay? I need the 'roids for myself.
-Shut up, Danny!

35:54.200 --> 35:55.269
Do it!

35:55.360 --> 35:56.759
What are you waiting for?
-Shut up!

36:02.120 --> 36:04.270
Where you going? Where you going?

36:05.240 --> 36:06.514
Please don't kill me.

36:14.560 --> 36:16.391
Freeze! Police!

36:17.440 --> 36:19.556
There was nothing going on.

36:23.520 --> 36:26.034
You all right?
-Yeah. My arm always bleeds like this.

36:26.120 --> 36:28.429
Oh, that's good. For a second there I
thought he broke your sarcasm bone.

36:28.520 --> 36:30.078
Sit down, man.

36:33.240 --> 36:35.708
It'll be okay.
-Thanks.

36:39.200 --> 36:41.509
Why is it always so complicated?

36:42.160 --> 36:46.438
You know, just wondering
who I am, what I am.

36:46.520 --> 36:49.876
You know, I used to ask myself
that a lot. Most people do.

36:49.960 --> 36:52.076
They spend their whole lives
trying to figure it out.

36:52.160 --> 36:53.479
You're pretty young, man.

36:53.560 --> 36:55.676
You seem like you got it together.
That's cool.

36:56.920 --> 37:01.994
Yeah, you sound like a cheesy pamphlet.
-Yeah, I do. AII right, it's a little lame.

37:02.640 --> 37:05.279
It doesn't mean it's not true.

37:11.360 --> 37:15.239
I'm sorry I didn't tell you before.
-It's okay. I understand.

37:18.280 --> 37:21.670
Lisa?
-I'll Ieave you guys alone.

37:23.480 --> 37:26.392
Hello, Mom.
- We've got an early flight.

37:27.480 --> 37:30.472
And I've set up an
appointment for you and me,

37:30.560 --> 37:33.836
for the two of us, honey,
with Dr Patterson.

37:33.920 --> 37:36.434
I don't need to see Dr Patterson.

37:36.520 --> 37:38.829
We can work this out together.

37:39.600 --> 37:44.628
I'll deal with what you want to be.
-I don't want you to deal with anything.

37:44.720 --> 37:48.395
Sweetheart, I love you.
I'm sorry. I've been wrong.

37:51.280 --> 37:54.875
I just want you to
accept me for who I am.

37:58.760 --> 38:05.108
I can't do that. I will. I'll try. Oh, God.

38:08.800 --> 38:13.669
I'm not going home with you.
-Please, don't say that.

38:16.040 --> 38:18.998
Lisa, you are everything to me.

38:20.000 --> 38:21.718
I love you.

38:23.320 --> 38:24.912
I love you, Mom.

38:27.360 --> 38:29.191
But my name is Daniel.

38:32.720 --> 38:35.029
I want to take you home with me.

38:36.800 --> 38:40.554
I think I have to stay here.
For now.

39:19.040 --> 39:20.075
Oz!
-Hey.

39:20.160 --> 39:21.149
Hey!
-You good?

39:21.240 --> 39:22.912
Yeah, we're good.

39:24.680 --> 39:28.070
Hey, how you doing? Osman Bey.
Oz for short, probably.

39:28.160 --> 39:30.674
You got two of us
on the Iist tonight.

39:30.760 --> 39:33.228
You gentlemen are not on the list, ja?

39:33.320 --> 39:37.791
No, no, no. Hold on. Hold on!
We saved Young Thunda's life, dawg. Sir.

39:37.880 --> 39:40.314
We saved his life.
That's all I'm saying. He's my boy.

39:41.960 --> 39:44.269
I'm not sure if he's holding up.

39:55.200 --> 39:57.156
Yo, Thunda in the house! Boo!

39:57.760 --> 39:58.988
